<TITLE> Govt decides to form 'core committee' on prices </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 23 (bdnews24.com)--The government Sunday decided to form a "core committee" to watch and guide the essential commodities market amid public discontent about a sharp rise in prices. The committee to be led by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed will name other members at its first meeting set for Tuesday. The decision came from a cabinet meeting at the Chief Adviser's Office, chaired by Fakhruddin. After the meeting, the CA's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told reporters that the advisers of food, finance, agriculture and commerce ministries would likely be on the committee. The committee will monitor food prices, stock, supply and import and make guidelines on the market to keep the situation in check. bdn
